content: Hello Jeyachandran! It's great to meet you. Welcome to the interview for the Software Engineer position at Google. I'm Master, your hiring officer. Before we begin, I want to thank you for taking the time to share your qualifications and experiences with me today. May I invite you to start by telling me a bit about yourself and why you're interested in this role at Google?
i am b.tech aiml in kec and i want to update my skills

Wonderful! So, you have a strong background in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning from Kongu Engineering College, KEC. That's fantastic! It's great that you're eager to update your skills and take on new challenges.

Can you walk me through some of the projects or hackathons you participated in during your academic tenure? Specifically, I'm interested in knowing more about your wins in the E-Horizon Hackathon, HackSphere Hackathon, Thinkathon, and Chat Genius. How did you approach those challenges, and what skills did you develop during those experiences?
You'd like to ask me a question, Jeyachandran. Go ahead, fire away! I'm happy to answer any questions you may have about the Software Engineer position or Google in general.
